---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import FlavorTabs from "../../../components/FlavorTabs.astro";
import ModuleHero from "../../../components/module/ModuleHero.astro";
import ModuleScenario from "../../../components/module/ModuleScenario.astro";
import ModuleFlowDiagram from "../../../components/module/ModuleFlowDiagram.astro";
import ModuleFooterNav from "../../../components/module/ModuleFooterNav.astro";
import ModuleRecap from "../../../components/module/ModuleRecap.astro";
import { flavor as gcp } from "../../../data/flavors/gcp";
import { flavor as aws } from "../../../data/flavors/aws";
import { flavor as azure } from "../../../data/flavors/azure";
import { flavor as oss } from "../../../data/flavors/oss";

const moduleId = "10-ingestion";
const entries = {
  gcp: gcp[moduleId],
  aws: aws[moduleId],
  azure: azure[moduleId],
  oss: oss[moduleId],
};
---

<BaseLayout title="10 · Ingestion">
  <article>
    <ModuleHero moduleId={moduleId}>
      <p>
        Every pipeline starts the same way regardless of cloud: get raw content — documents, tickets, chats, web
        pages — into durable object storage, then register enough metadata (source, filename, ingested-at,
        checksum) in a table so later stages can find it and avoid re-processing duplicates.
      </p>
    </ModuleHero>

    <ModuleScenario moduleId={moduleId} />

    <ModuleFlowDiagram moduleId={moduleId} />

    <h2>Why object storage first, not straight to a vector DB</h2>
    <p>
      Parsing, OCR, and chunking strategies all change over time — you will re-run them. Keeping the original raw
      file in cheap object storage means every downstream stage is replayable from source, instead of being a
      one-way trip into an index you can't reconstruct.
    </p>

    <h2>Idempotency</h2>
    <p>
      Re-running an ingestion job on the same source must not create duplicate rows. The minimal pattern: hash the
      raw file, use the hash (or a stable source ID) as part of the storage key, and let a duplicate write short-circuit
      with a "already ingested" outcome rather than silently doubling your document count.
    </p>

    <h2>Try it in your flavor</h2>
    <FlavorTabs moduleId={moduleId} entries={entries} />

    <h2>Pitfalls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Skipping metadata (source, timestamp, checksum) — you'll need it for dedup, ACLs, and debugging retrieval later.</li>
      <li>Ingesting straight into a vector index with no raw-file copy — you lose the ability to re-chunk or re-embed later.</li>
      <li>No idempotency check — re-running a job during development silently multiplies your document count.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
  <ModuleRecap moduleId={moduleId} />
  <ModuleFooterNav moduleId={moduleId} />
</BaseLayout>
